<subSubSection id="7A0D8441414046D2235B50AB5E7411C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4445DE49BAAF76F48D3E1E7E9B0516AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7576170933B1CED2DB6B9CD33FBE2936" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="9762883EBB0C2B20F530527A8D7ADD2A" authorityName="Xu &amp; Liu &amp; Li" authorityYear="2021" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Gigantochloa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gigantochloa glabrata" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glabrata">
<emphasis id="1090B2DF8F0172EE21703768B5BA2114" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Gigantochloa glabrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has erect culm sheath blade and the culm sheath covered with sparsely deciduous setae, with truncate apex. It is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D15A03DC351482757A77688CEC426FBC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="G. albociliata" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="albociliata">
<emphasis id="E2EF58020A3651EC50F13FBEA91D4D78" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">G. albociliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B8655537523C0BDA31B6D46CD9D7A797" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="G. levis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="levis">
<emphasis id="6509ECA74160E70694937898392D5295" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">G. levis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily distinguished from them by having erect blades; culm sheath ligule 4-6 mm high, truncate, denticulate; a ring of white tomentum on the intranode and below the node (Table 
<tableCitation id="0C3181F1D81E5B3A320BBD9E6C62FC9F" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological differences between Gigantochloa glabrata, G. albociliata and G. levis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0F4C41E2311E4EA3D9AEE64137D9B9F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" tableUuid="0F4C41E2311E4EA3D9AEE64137D9B9F1">1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="0F4C41E2311E4EA3D9AEE64137D9B9F1" ID-Table-UUID="0F4C41E2311E4EA3D9AEE64137D9B9F1" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0F4C41E2311E4EA3D9AEE64137D9B9F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" start="Table 1" startId="T1">
